com.twitter.elephantbird.pig.load
Class LzoSlice

java.lang.Object
  com.twitter.elephantbird.pig.load.LzoSlice
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, org.apache.pig.Slice
public class LzoSlice
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.pig.Slice

This class implements the Pig Slice interface, meaning it both represents an input split and begins processing on a mapper by binding a loader to each input split.

Constructor Detail

LzoSlice

public LzoSlice(java.lang.String filename,
                long start,
                long length,
                org.apache.pig.FuncSpec loadFuncSpec)
Construct a slice with the given specifications.

Parameters:
filename - the filename from which the block comes.
start - the byte offset of the start of the block. If this is zero, it's necessary to read the file header before real data reading starts. If this is nonzero, it's assumed to be at the beginning of an LZO block boundary, otherwise decompression will fail.
length - the length of the block.
loadFuncSpec - the spec for invoking the loader function.
